Skyline 16 Days trek to the ‘Everest Base Camp’.

Our Everest Base Camp trek, which we have been successfully organizing since past two decades, starts with a breathtaking flight from Kathmandu to Lukla. Right after we land at Lukla, we trek up to the Dudh Koshi Valley, enclosed by the sky-high peaks of Thamserku and Kusum Kanguru. It’s a steep ascent to Namche Bazaar, capital of the Khumbu Sherpa’s, where we are bestowed with the breathtakingly beautiful mountain views. A rest day here aids acclimatization and there are great optional walks to explore and enjoy the rich culture of the local people. The trail then follows the famous Tengboche, located high on a ridge where a splendid 360 degree panorama awaits. The views of Mighty Everest, ‘the Lhotse Nuptse wall, Ama Dablam and Kantega dominates this tranquil and spiritual site. The early morning view from Tengboche is absolutely superlative and mesmerizing that captivates you with its memories that lasts a lifetime.

What makes our Everest Base Camp package stand out from the rest?

Skyline’s two weeks of challenging and rewarding trek to Everest base camp lets you enjoy the spectacular beauty of the nature at its best, while also enabling you to experience the hospitable Nepalese culture and tradition. We stay in tea-houses that give cozy places to stay along the way. In order to make travelers stay in Nepal more remarkable, we specially allow enough time to ascend Kalapattar ‘the prime view spot’to Mount Everest with an elevation of 8,848 meters.

From the captivating beauty of snow-capped mountains, bulky rocks, beautiful landscapes, wildlife experience, wide ecological diversity to rich and profound cultures of the local people ‘The Everest Camp Trek’ package has it all to create memories to last you a life-time.

If you have any additional queries about the trekking package, feel free to contact us online! We at Skyline will try our level best to provide you the best trekking services to Nepal. We appreciate your feedback.
